e on Quebec's possible separation from the rest of Canada began, to the present, in which the traditional cultural heritage has been further fragmented by the increasing presence of diasporic communities. His career and films offer an ideal case study for exploring the contradictions and tensions that have shaped Quebec cinema and culture in a period of increasing globalization and technological change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszQuébec (Province)vBiography. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aForeign-Language, Canada, Film, Quebec: French Language, Culture, Catholic, Faith, Modern Society, Tradition, Technology, Globalization, Technological Change, Denys Arcand, crime, Media Studies, Communications, Social Science, Arts, videos, Entertainment, video production, Criticism, French Language.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069033040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081359890140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813598901423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813598901/original  a978-3-11-069033-0  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK